13.4.6 Exercises

1

airports %>%
  semi_join(flights, c("faa" = "dest")) %>%
  ggplot(aes(lon, lat)) +
    borders("state") +
    geom_point() +
    coord_quickmap()

flights %>% group_by(dest) %>%
  summarize(avg_arr_delay = mean(arr_delay, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  left_join(airports, by = c('dest' = 'faa')) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = lon, y = lat, size = avg_arr_delay, color = avg_arr_delay)) +
  borders('state') +
  geom_point() +
  coord_quickmap()

2

flights %>% 
  left_join(airports, by = c('dest' = 'faa')) %>%
  left_join(airports, by = c('origin' = 'faa'), suffix = c('.dest', '.origin')) %>%
  select(dest, origin, contains('lat'), contains('lon'))

3

flights %>% group_by(tailnum) %>%
  summarise(avg_dep_delay = mean(dep_delay, na.rm = TRUE),
            avg_arr_delay = mean(arr_delay, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  gather(key = 'mode', value = 'delay', 2:3) %>%
  left_join(planes, by = 'tailnum') %>%
  ggplot(mapping = aes(x = year, y = delay)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE) +
  facet_grid(.~mode)

Its hard to make a comparison.

4

flights %>% 
  left_join(weather, by = c('year','month','day','hour','origin')) %>%
  gather(key = 'condition', value = 'value', temp:visib) %>%
  filter(!is.na(dep_delay)) %>%
  ggplot(mapping = aes(x = value, y = dep_delay)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~condition, ncol = 3, scale = 'free_x')

There is not any strong correlation.

13.5.1 Exercises

1

flights %>%
  filter(is.na(tailnum))

For a flight to have a missing tailnum means that that flight was cancelled.

flights %>%
  anti_join(planes, by = 'tailnum') %>%
  group_by(carrier) %>%
  summarize(n = n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(n))

The tail numbers that dont have a matching record in planes come from the same two carriers.

2

flights %>%
  semi_join(count(flights, tailnum) %>% filter(n >= 100))
Joining, by = "tailnum"

3

ten_common <-
  fueleconomy::common %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  arrange(-n) %>%
  top_n(10, n)
fueleconomy::vehicles %>%
  semi_join(ten_common)
Joining, by = c("make", "model")

4

fn <-flights %>%
  group_by(month, day) %>%
  summarize(avg_delay = sum(arr_delay + dep_delay, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  mutate(twoday_delay = avg_delay + lag(avg_delay)) %>%
  arrange(-twoday_delay)
wea <-weather %>%
  group_by(month, day) %>%
  summarize_at(vars(humid, precip, temp), mean, na.rm = TRUE)
fn %>%
  left_join(wea) %>%
  arrange(twoday_delay)
Joining, by = c("month", "day")

5

It shows flights whose destinations are not included in the airports database. It shows the airport names and locations that the flights from flights are not flying to.

  summarize(n = length(unique(carrier))) %>%
  filter(n > 1)
